e missing auth, branch, or diff-shape issues in the live platform (MOCK-HIDE yes). Not LLM/agentic.","test_description":"Run end-to-end PR creation against a dedicated real test repository, then verify via repository API/UI that one PR exists, branch contains only the intended dependency bump, and diff shows a single-dependency change.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.0,"Integration":0.03,"System":0.97,"Agentic":0.0,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":6,"description":"A major version bump is correctly identified as a breaking change based on semver comparison.","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"Semver comparison is local deterministic logic with no module or infrastructure dependency required (MOCK-MISS no; REAL-INFRA no; LLM-DEP no). Higher levels are disqualified because behavior text is purely about semantic version classification.","test_description":"Test semver comparator with representative version pairs (major/minor/patch/pre-release) and assert breaking-change flag is true only for major increases per semver rules.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.95,"Integration":0.05,"System":0.0,"Agentic":0.0,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":7,"description":"When a breaking change is detected, PR creation is skipped and a review flag is surfaced in the scanner output.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure boundary is orchestration/state handoff across modules: semver decision -> PR service gate -> output/reporting (MOCK-MISS yes). System was considered but rejected because behavior text is about skipping PR and surfacing a flag; this can be verified with an in-process PR client stub/spies plus output assertion, without real network/OS dependency (REAL-INFRA no). No AI/LLM and no multi-agent sequence.","test_description":"Wire scanner service with real decision/report modules and a spy/stub PR client, feed a manifest update that is a breaking major bump